locality: Mpio. El Salto. Sierra Madre Occidental: rim of plateau W of La Ciudad, 3.1 km NW of Hwy 40 (Durango-Mazatlan) off Neveros rd, upper Arroyo Tascanto watershed. Wooded plateau & steep to overhanging cliffs & moist canyon below (w/seep), W to NW-facing escarpment; pine-oak woodl. w/Abies durangensis, Pinus dur., Prunus ser., Quercus sid., Hydrangea s., Arbutus, etc.
Near the microwave towers atop Volcán Tequila south of Tequila, 13 miles south of Mexico Highway 15 and 11 miles south of the railroad in Tequila.
